<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: 2.2.7:  <p>
I just used the floor inscription 'dunna hrassa' for probably the first time ever, and saw the following message: 
</p>
<p>
<tt>A&nbsp;chasm&nbsp;appears&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;floor!&nbsp;The&nbsp;monster&nbsp;fall&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;chasm&nbsp;!</tt> 
</p>
<p>
It needs to be "falls", and delete the space between "chasm" and the exclamation point. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: This error was also reported also in <a class="nonexistent" href="./BugReport118">BugReport118</a>. Fixed in ToME 2.3.0 (CVS). 
</p>
